values:
Renouncers and Jainism. 
Micro organisms and the like.
Social standards and standing upright.
Alfred University shirts made in Uganda for me. 

Moksha and the cause. India, you were never very interesting to me after the british colonized you. Now, you are precious in your polytheistic ways. Seeing India through the eyes of India. Still wouldn't want to go there.

I am made of barbeque sauce.
I'm so balanced right now.
I work out a lot, my mind is very clear.
I am very motivated.
My room is still very dirty.
But I washed SOME dishes, and I hate doing that normally.

Will you dance with me?
Um...
Say yes.
Yes.
Good.

When you've always wanted a puppy and got one on your twelveth birthday, you should count your blessings.

And on that same day when a silly old teenager decided to test how fast his car was...you should forsake your blessings and play tictactoe on his shiny green hood.

And then, when no one's looking. You should kill his petunias. 

-Lexball

P.S.
If he hasn't got petunias, kill his mother.

Violet, the color reserved only for The Caesar. It is deep and aged, meant for contemplation and wisdom. Its complement is yellow, the color for insanity and intelligence. Strange how such things are.

Anyone caught in violet was punished. The color was not theirs, owned by another. 

My nightgown is violet tonight. For a moment, I feared of being caught. I laugh at myself now. But if I were, would I escape by saying that I don't mean to testify my ownership on this hue, I mean to state its ownership on me. And since YOU own this color, you own my very being.

But I won't be caught, foolish thoughts for a normally wise girl. I don't mean to flatter, but being Caesar gives you certain privileges.
